entry.title: The Islington Primary Care Trust (Establishment) Order 2002
entry.summary: This Order establishes the Islington Primary Care Trust (“the trust”), as provided for under section 16A of the National Health Service Act 1977. It specifies the trust’s establishment and operational dates (article 2) and the area for which it is established (article 3 and the Schedule).

entry.title: The Town and Country Planning (Fees for Applications and Deemed Applications) (Amendment) (England) Regulations 2002
entry.summary: These regulations further amend the Town and Country Planning (Fees for Applications and Deemed Applications) Regulations 1989.

entry.title: The Sheep and Goats Identification and Movement (Interim Measures) (England) (Amendment) Order 2002
entry.summary: This Order applies only to England. It amends the Sheep and Goats Identification and Movement (Interim Measures) (England) Order 2002 (S.I. 2002/240) (the principal Order), which for a temporary period until 30th November 2002 imposes requirements relating to the identification, registration and movement of sheep and goats.

entry.title: The Value Added Tax (Health and Welfare) Order 2002
entry.summary: This Order, which comes into force on 21st March 2002, amends Group 7 of Schedule 9 to the Value Added Tax Act 1994 (c. 23). Group 7 makes provision for the exemption of the supply of health and welfare services.

entry.title: The Teddington, Twickenham and Hamptons Primary Care Trust (Establishment) Amendment and Change of Name Order 2002
entry.summary: This Order amends the establishment Order of the Teddington, Twickenham and Hamptons Primary Care Trust (“the trust”), a Primary Care Trust established by Order under section 16A of the National Health Service Act 1977 by increasing from 5 to 6 the number of officer members, and by increasing from 5 to 6 the number of non-officer members.

entry.title: The Nurses, Midwives and Health Visitors (Professional Conduct) (Amendment) (No. 2) Rules 2002, Approval Order (Northern Ireland) 2002
entry.summary: This Order approves, as respects proceedings in Northern Ireland only, the Rules set out in the Schedule. These amend the Professional Conduct rules of the United Kingdom Central Council for Nursing, Midwifery and Health Visiting so as to reduce the number of medical examiners who are required to examine the practitioner from two to one in cases concerning the practitioner’s fitness to practice; and to make further provision with respect to any medical practitioner instructed by the practitioner.

entry.title: The National Health Service Pension Scheme (Additional Voluntary Contributions) Amendment Regulations 2002

ukm:Subject.Value: NATIONAL HEALTH SERVICE, ENGLAND AND WALES

category.term: NATIONAL HEALTH SERVICE, ENGLAND AND WALES

entry.summary: These Regulations amend the National Health Service Pension Scheme (Additional Voluntary Contributions) Regulations 2000 (“the AVC Regulations”) which provide for the payment of additional voluntary contributions by persons who are members of the pension scheme constituted by the National Health Service Pension Scheme Regulations 1995 (“the Pension Scheme Regulations”), or by their employers, in order to secure additional benefits financed by investment of those contributions.

entry.title: The General Chiropractic Council (Election of Members and Chairman of Council) Rules Order 2002
entry.summary: This Order, which is made under the Chiropractors Act 1994, approves Rules made by the General Chiropractic Council (“the Council”) which provide for the procedure both for the election of registered chiropractors as members of the Council for the period following the end of the transitional period mentioned in paragraphs 43 and 44 of Schedule 1 to the Act and for the election of a Chairman of the Council.

entry.title: The Nelson and West Merton Primary Care Trust (Establishment) Amendment and Change of Name Order 2002
entry.summary: This Order amends the establishment order of the Nelson and West Merton Primary Care Trust (“the trust”), a Primary Care Trust established by Order under section 16A of the National Health Service Act 1977.

entry.title: Local Government Pension Scheme (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2002
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Local Government Pension Scheme Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2000 (“the principal Regulations”).

entry.title: The Civil Legal Aid (Financial Conditions) (Scotland) Regulations 2002
entry.summary: These Regulations increase certain of the financial limits of eligibility for civil legal aid under the Legal Aid (Scotland) Act 1986.

entry.title: The Northallerton Health Services National Health Service Trust (Dissolution) Order 2002
entry.summary: This version of the The Northallerton Health Services National Health Service Trust (Dissolution) Order 2002 is published under the authority and superintendence of the Queen's Printer of Acts of Parliament and Controller of HMSO. It has been prepared to reflect the text as it was Made.

entry.title: The South Tees Acute Hospitals National Health Service Trust (Establishment) Amendment Order 2002
entry.summary: This Order further amends the South Tees Acute Hospitals National Health Service Trust (Establishment) Order 1991, which established the South Tees Acute Hospitals National Health Service Trust.

entry.title: The Removal and Disposal of Vehicles (England) (Amendment) Regulations 2002
entry.summary: The Removal and Disposal of Vehicles Regulations 1986 (“the 1986 Regulations”) provide for the removal and disposal of vehicles under sections 3 and 4 of the Refuse Disposal (Amenity) Act 1978 and sections 99 and 101 of the Road Traffic Regulation Act 1984. These Regulations amend the 1986 Regulations in England to reduce the period of notice prescribed by the Regulations in two cases.

entry.title: The A21 Trunk Road (A2100 Junction Improvement John’s Cross) Order 2002
entry.summary: This version of the The A21 Trunk Road (A2100 Junction Improvement John’s Cross) Order 2002 is published under the authority and superintendence of the Queen's Printer of Acts of Parliament and Controller of HMSO. It has been prepared to reflect the text as it was Made.

entry.title: The A21 Trunk Road (A2100 Junction Improvement John’s Cross) (Detrunking) Order 2002
entry.summary: This version of the The A21 Trunk Road (A2100 Junction Improvement John’s Cross) (Detrunking) Order 2002 is published under the authority and superintendence of the Queen's Printer of Acts of Parliament and Controller of HMSO. It has been prepared to reflect the text as it was Made.

entry.title: The Education (Bursaries for School Teacher Training) (England) (Amendment) Regulations 2002
entry.summary: These Regulations correct two defects in the Education (Bursaries for School Teacher Training) (England) Regulations 2002.

entry.title: The South West Yorkshire Mental Health National Health Service Trust (Establishment) and the Wakefield and Pontefract Community National Health Service Trust (Dissolution) Order 2002
entry.summary: This Order establishes the South West Yorkshire Mental Health National Health Service Trust as an NHS trust, provided for in section 5 of the National Health Service and Community Care Act 1990.

entry.title: The Bradford District Care Trust (Establishment) and the Bradford Community Health National Health Service Trust (Dissolution) Order 2002
entry.summary: This Order establishes the Bradford District Care Trust as an NHS trust designated as a Care Trust, as provided for in section 5 of the National Health Service and Community Care Act 1990 and section 45 of the Health and Social Care Act 2001.
